  "doc_id": "2211",
  "text": "An MMV n -algebra introduced in [44, Definition 3.1] is an algebra of Lukasiewicz n-valued modal logic. We then have the following. Proof. By Teheux representation following from [CITATION_1] Theorem 4.11] , any MMV n -algebra can be embedded into a modal power of n. It is straightforward to see that any A ∈ ISP M (n) is an MMV n -algebra. Thus, ISP M (2) coincides with the class of all modal algebras. It follows from Proposition 3.14 below that ISP M (n) satisfies the Kripke condition (or this also follows from the completeness of Lukasiewicz n-valued modal logic).",
